race.comment: BELLA CHINKARA (10) got off the mark when resuming from a spell over 1200m here and did it comfortably as favourite. May be able to sit closer today and has more up her sleeve. Nicely placed to double the win tally. SOUTHERN AURORAS (6) won a Maiden by a space here three back and has been narrowly beaten at the track the two since. Peaks on a 7-day return back a grade and the extra 200m isn't an issue. ILOVETHISTOWN (1) deserved his easy heavily-bet Maiden win and can build on that. Has an awkward gate but the 3kg claim benefits. ARGYLL DIAMOND (7) is another last start Maiden winner at the track and did it well enough to consider. Ditto REDAIR (11) from a low gate with a top hoop sticking aboard.
